text: A few questions to game designers:  "I do not wish to play as a racer. Why am I obliged to do the racer tutorial, and why is it unskippable? Why am I forced to play through the tutorial for BOTH cop and racer and have no choice, nor the option to get to the menu and save while doing so, which makes it impossible to quit the game in the middle of the tutorial, because the next time I am launching it, I have to watch the opening cutscene AGAIN and the whole tutorial from the beginning? Whose genius idea was this?"  Also,   "Why can't I enjoy my singleplayer experience now?.. There is no pause available, so in this game, playing singleplayer is like playing multiplayer with invisible players, as all the online rules still apply to me only. Which means that if something in the real world demands my attention, I can not stop the game and continue it later, and if I have to do something quickly outside of the game, I'm destined to crash into something in game, or to lose the race or pursuit. Logic?.."

text: So lemme make a formula that would make people equally content, unless they really want to eliminate the other totally: 1: Cars - Tuners would be exclusive to many customization options including body kits, spoilers, neons, audio, and even custom headlights. Some of them are offroad capable while others are perfect drifters. - Musclecars would be the dragsters, and would be modified and upgraded as such. - Exotics would be the top speed (Not acceleration like Muscles, or Grip like Tuners) custom rims, and custom paint job, and performance upgrades are minimal, but would not go further than that, being what they are. 2: racing - Urban and rural, enough said. I mean, why not having both city racing and rural racing, with deserts, coastals, mountainsides, and other beautiful environments to sight-see? - Be-the-cop mode would be best with MW's pursuit system. Cruise, find a racer, arrest them with a squad of them, as others block the road. Order Rhinos, spikes, etc. 3: Online/offline - EA's tries to make online only nfs-es are getting old, especially with each race being so randomly selected. The reason we all loved Multiplayers was none of such nonsense, but the fact there was a race host, and the other players, and they decided together what race was next. Also, why not allowing players with no internet connection or will to race against other people, to play it offline? Ability to pause.

text: As a racer you only get to use 22 cars.   The speedlist are silly. For example one objective will ask you to get a spikestrip hit.   You stay idle.. drop a spike strip... then reverse over it. Objective complete.   Another will ask you to get a gold in 3 events. When you gold an event you can restart it another 2 times to complete this objective. Silly  You constantly resume pursuits which you have just escaped when there are no police around.   While you are in a pursuit,  you can escape it but entering a hide out while in the pursuit. Easy.  You get no trophy for collecting all collectibles.   There is no story mode. Just missions.  And get this.. you can't ever pause the game.. EVER!  Need for speed games are looking better but the actual game isn't getting better. This game is the best looking racer by far. The last need for speed game which was good was the 2010 Hot Pursuit.

author: Gabriel S

text: EA COME ON, ENOUGH IS ENOUGH! YOU HAVE BEEN PLEADED AND EVEN BEGGED BY TENS OF THOUSANDS OF NEED FOR SPEED FANS, YET YOU CONTINUE TO IGNORE US. THE GLORY DAYS OF NEED FOR SPEED WERE DURING UNDERGROUND, UNDERGROUND 2, MOST WANTED AND CARBON. THE LOYAL FANS HAVE BEEN SO PATIENT. ALL WE WANT IS AN UNDERGROUND 3, or MOST WANTED 2 or CARBON 2 TYPE GAME.  I really miss being able to custom tune my ride, having to verse other street racers to scrape up some cash to upgrade my engine, or spoiler. Let's face it, the series has greatly declined since the end of the classic phase (underground - undercover) and unless an underground 3 is made, the series will inevitably die off. Please, for the sake of the fans, for the sake of the classic nfs series, please go back to the street racing games that we could spend hours on end playing'

When you speed above 300 kmh the feeling is more realistic, there is also no motion blur, to make you think you are fast af.
